and supercritical, respectively.

The Penrose diagrams we have determined so far ()
had two separate pieces, each corresponding to one side of the
domain wall, along with a prescription for identifying the points
on the bubble wall to join the two pieces together. This might be
sufficient for our purposes since we know how to map the points of
the domain wall from one part of the Penrose diagram to the other.
However, it may still be interesting to see how to construct one
global (and connected) Penrose diagram from the two parts. In
order to do so, we will have to perform a (conformal) coordinate
transformation at least on one side.



