. The two vertical edges of the diagram should be
identified because the spatial slice of the global geometry is a
circle. The picture shows  one static patch, which is the causal
patch of an observer originating in  and arriving at , and
another static patch, which is the causal patch of someone
starting at  and going to . All the static patches are
equivalent up to actions of the  de Sitter group.
  
