Clearly there are many interesting ways to deviate from and refine
these choices, but we will see that these specifications are
sufficient to answer the most basic questions we are interested in
regarding the entropy comparisons. In the following, the symbol
 will refer to relations that hold up to coefficients that
are of order one, by which we mean coefficients which do not go to
zero or infinity as we scale up the RR flux quantum numbers.

